Author: Sunopsis Version: 4.0 Last Update: DEC-2004
Description: - Loading Knowledge Module - This LKM transfers data between two AS/400 machines. It uses CRTDDMF to create a DDM file on the target and transfers data from the work table (on the source) to this DDM file using CPYF.
Restriction: - This KM uses system calls on AS/400, and requires to have the agent installed on the target AS/400 machine. - Journalizing Options are not implemented in this module. - To use this IKM, the temporary (C$, I$...) and target tables should be stored in AS400 collections (or AS400 journalized libraries), otherwise, an SQL7008 message will be signalled (refer to the IBM DB2/400 documentation for details concerning SQLCode 7008). - The name of the tables (C$...) must not be greater than 10 characters
Set this option to NO if you wish to retain temporary objects (tables, files and scripts) after integration. Useful for debugging.
Insert into work table on source
